Citation.sTitle: Solubility of a-Carotene in Binary Solvents Formed by Some Hydrocarbons with tert-Butyl Methyl Ether and with tert-Amyl Methyl Ether
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental results are reported for the solubility of a-carotene in six binary mixed solvents formed by tert-butyl methyl ether or tert-amyl methyl ether with cyclohexane, hexane, and toluene at 293.15 K. A spectral colorimeter was used for the analysis of a-carotene concentration. The a-carotene solubility in the pure solvents increases in the order hexane less than tert-butyl methyl ether less than tert-amyl methyl ether less than cyclohexane less than toluene. The solubility data as a function of the binary solvent mole fractions were correlated by the Myers and Scott equation. Results of these measurements were used to test the predictive ability of a-carotene solubility in the binary mixed solvents using the Treszczanowicz and the Acree and Rytting models. Both models qualitatively predict the solubility of a-carotene in the above-mentioned mixed solvents.
